-MXPNVrCZvs1DOc5eDYr.name: Bumazhnaya Ved'ma aka Granny Buma
-MXPNVrCZvs1DOc5eDYr.special: You are undead and so do not need to breathe or circulate blood. You take double Damage from Silver Weapons and regain Stamina half as effectively from all sources. You must Test your Luck if outside in the rain, are made wet, are close to open flames, or suffer generally grievous wounds. A failure will see your skin ruined. If your skin is compromised you are very obviously a walking corpse.

-MZbGLFG47jCFNYxUYwZ.name: Ray
-MZbGLFG47jCFNYxUYwZ.special: When trying to last one more minute on the Creek and failing a roll would result in you falling in the Creek you may attempt a Balance roll - on a success you do not fall in the Creek but must retry the challenge.

-MZbQiYM_5TreOMMd5-K.name: Jude
-MZbQiYM_5TreOMMd5-K.special: When you attempt to cast a spell without the appropriate advanced skill you must use an item from your bag of components. You cannot attempt to cast that spell again until the item you used has been readded to the bag or until you have formally studied the spell.

-MZbZJsfYRRJB16v4jxA.name: Tony
-MZbZJsfYRRJB16v4jxA.special: As a cloud of living words you take half damage from weapons that do not bypass armour.

-M_Bu0EHjJrutihvnRow.name: Sam Smith (They/Them)
-M_Bu0EHjJrutihvnRow.special: When you lose your last medal, you are no longer a Duelist, lose the right to wield your pistolets. Gain or lose medals in sanctioned competition. Medals may be sought by non-duelists to sell, gaining medals after ceasing to be a Duelist is purely for monatary worth.

-MbU2vEzucjbQYadcC1d.background: Vengeful Child - I seek vengeance against Ek, the 8-headed snake who devoured my village. My family were field mouse farmers. I will also kill the blue screech owl. I will also kill the fellow in the broze mask, who ambushed us with rocks.The wizard tuned out to not be vengance worthy. Barb the slug person is very nice.
-MbU2vEzucjbQYadcC1d.name: Kore
-MbU2vEzucjbQYadcC1d.special:
Too-large Sword

+++Reduce to 12 items in inventor (not provisions, money, candy)+++

-MdAIfYkMg6896XajRAW.background: Temple Knight of Telak the Swordbringer
-MdAIfYkMg6896XajRAW.name: Harpe (new and improved)
-MdAIfYkMg6896XajRAW.special:
The blessing of Telak awards you Armour equal to half (rounded down) the number of Swords you carry. If you carried 6 Swords your Armour would be 3 while if you carried 9 it would be 4.

You must be overtly armed at all times or else Telak will take this blessing away until you forge and donate to the unarmed a brand new Sword.

He's 5' 3" and 90 lbs.

-Mg5YKm8QGLZc2f8mFU0.name: Thimble
-Mg5YKm8QGLZc2f8mFU0.special: You have parted from your folk and their righteous fury. You have left your home and the high aeries, never to return. A bird with broken wings is better off than one in a cage.

-MgV7OZXFGGaVEjquu_R.name: Kurt Carnap
-MgV7OZXFGGaVEjquu_R.special:
Mathmologists honour the clean and unambiguous truths of mathematics and coordinate them with their observations of the multiverse. All things can be measured and predicted with the application of the correct mathmological ratios, those methods applied to penetrate the ethereal
surface and glimpse the fundamental numbers below.

-MgVBFocD6HJ2Ngm_3H3.name: Tony
-MgVBFocD6HJ2Ngm_3H3.special:
Special
You are immune to all mind altering effects. You are able to speak but usually choose not to. When making Advancement Checks for Skills related to abstract thought, such as Spells or Astrology, you must roll twice and succeed on both to improve them.

-MgVE0G8vB4ROnO_1p6X.name: Lord Bubbington
-MgVE0G8vB4ROnO_1p6X.special: You  are  Those-Filthy-Born,  spawned  in   the   hump-backed   sky   lit   only   by  great  black  anti-suns  and  false  light.   Your   mother   was   sailing   on   the  golden  barges  or  caught  in  some  more  abstract  fate  when  she  passed  you,  far  from  the  protective  malaise  of   the   million   Spheres.   You   were   receptive  to  the  power  and  the  glory  at  a  generative  time  and  it  shows  in  your teratoid form.

-MgXpmREuwAe_JBE5yTA.name: Cadius Odastrum
-MgXpmREuwAe_JBE5yTA.special:
Wandering miracle workers, the depths of whose clothes are filled with pouches of unguents, holy icons and herbs. No matter the metaphysical need, you are always prepared. 

Can pass through plants as if they are immaterial.

Viscaridormus -- God of Hibernation and Intestines (Sleep is important for good digestion) 
-- can bank sleep

-MhwlRJwwWNw-7BKvPzD.name: Swan Mother 'Smuther' (They/She)
-MhwlRJwwWNw-7BKvPzD.special: You may pluck d66 Feathers from your wings to summon a Swan that is under your control. Your Swans act on your Initiative. You can communicate with your Swans and issue them commands that they will follow. Keep track of the number of Feathers that your wings have left. If you run out of Feathers your Swans vanish to a far realm in a puff of smoke and glitter and you lose your Fly skill. When you eat 100 fish your wings grow back with 666 Golden Feathers.

-MhwmmiUvS6uGG-_UpU6.name: Grumbus
-MhwmmiUvS6uGG-_UpU6.special:
Rat-eating stowaway. Likes to read.

You take double Damage from silver weapons and regain Stamina half as effectively from all sources. Also, take a -2 penalty on all skill rolls where physical beauty would affect the result.

In reality, most vampires are this ugly.

-MhwoBVy-tp72evYWpke.name: SYNC [They/Them]
-MhwoBVy-tp72evYWpke.special:
SYNC, the vaporwave space skeleton :3

"(While skellies do not wear armor, they only take 2 STAMINA damage from any attack that is meant to pierce, puncture or slash. They can’t be suffocated or poisoned)."

"Most reanimated skeletons literally don’t have the brains they were born with. A few retain intelligence after being reanimated, or perhaps a runaway soul uses the bones as a hiding place. These skeletons are often put to use as marksmen, as their eyeless sockets do not water from wind and smoke, and their hands do not tremble with fear or agitation. Intelligent skeletons (or ‘skellies’ as the goblins call them) are often quite gregarious, and as their fleshless kin do not speak much, try to fit in among the living."

[Art by YouLookLikeFOOD DA]

-MhwoCNUA7cy7_ul7aMA.name: gary
-MhwoCNUA7cy7_ul7aMA.special:
i'm a cook y'all

You are a veteran of many voyages and an essential member of any astronef crew. It is often no mean feat to wring something edible from the bounty of the spontaneous generation vats, and occasionally, you succeed.

-Ml2r3p__Kh9lpvYgwst.name: Kip Spannerman
-Ml2r3p__Kh9lpvYgwst.special: You were a mercenary retained in the exclusive service of the Phoenix Throne, handsomely paid and sent to distant spheres on golden ships to spread the ineffable glory of your lords at the tip of your flaming sword.

-MnwlQxRvdModRNCuXEM.name: Kango
-MnwlQxRvdModRNCuXEM.special:
Unburdened: Armor is always at three so long as Kango wears no armor. If he is caught by suprise, his armor is considered 0. Fists count as Maces.

Holy Mantra: 3 Temporary HP per day, +1 armor to all comrades (up to 3), -1 armor to self. Must be intoned or chanted.

(smol) Dwarf: +4 to encumberance  + Darkvision +Slow but steady: Move 20 feet instead of 30, unaffected by encumberance up to 3 over total + 2 to trapping

Racist - Hated by elves greenskins, giants, and gobblers of all kinds.

-Mqb8ENypQOHQ3ZIKmp6.name: P.C. Erik Brett Henry Griffiths Brabantio
-Mqb8ENypQOHQ3ZIKmp6.special: The Key Masters wander the universe fathoming the workings of all entryways. Though they’re quite fascinated with simple chests and doors they are most excited by metaphysical and metaphorical barriers. You might find small conclaves of Clavigers camped around the feet of Demon Gates, debating appropriate methods of attack, or building obscure machines of entry.

-MT6tnjnqlqA_iDKiPqC.description: Requires twenty minutes to set up and use but doesn’t need to be outside. Consists of a ruby specular, charms against reciprocal observation, and complicated charts of the spheres. Grants +1 to Astrology.
-MT6tnjnqlqA_iDKiPqC.name: Astrological Equipment

Rory: 3/9

Horse (Silver)
 Carrying:my lance, and a lantern, and Rory, cactus parts

Rory the party mandrill -- henchman

Tendralina - Fresh Gilding Metropolous - Data Nodules - Empty City - Why was it destroyed?

-MTBHwXCL-7cw2zfnLA9.description: An Epopt’s Staff is a tool, an advert, and, in a pinch, a Weapon. In its head is set a cloudy ruby, like a useless magnifying glass, which grants the user +1 Second Sight while peering through it.
-MTBHwXCL-7cw2zfnLA9.name: Epopt's Staff

-MTBHwXDiq0AbJTeeydm.description: A Fusil can also be used as a club.
-MTBHwXDiq0AbJTeeydm.name: Fusil (Melee)

-MTBHwXEaKrm2f83DkjG.description: A fusil is a long Weapon that looks like a rifle and can be used in melee as a Club. A Fusil holds 6 charges before the plasmic core needs replacing.
-MTBHwXEaKrm2f83DkjG.name: Fusil (Ranged)

-MTSUqQFbAm9RIwwMkfR.description: Requires twenty minutes to set up and use but doesn’t need to be outside. Consists of a ruby specular, charms against reciprocal observation, and complicated charts of the spheres. Grants +1 to Astrology.

-MV9PfIrg_FAeg5SVZ0P.name: Hotel Pamphlet

-MVA6QB7nA3sGYhbPtJ-.name: Cage Match at the Center of the Universe Home Game

-MXPeDxVKokOsc5HprXD.description: Ruby lorgnettes are collapsable spectacles made with ruby lenses that require a free hand to use. While wearing them your sight is impaired but you can see sorcerous activity clearly (+2 Second Sight).
-MXPeDxVKokOsc5HprXD.name: Ruby Lorgnettes

-MXNHC-4QGF6hQYDMDTj.description: A bale hook counts as a Knife for Damage and grants +1 on rolls to lift heavy objects.
-MXNHC-4QGF6hQYDMDTj.name: Bale Hook

-Mu3M6bFyZNB1Q5Nrjn0.description: Plasmic cores are crystalised starlight cast in metal. Or astral vapours captured in glass. Or maybe hard-ghosts? Whatever it is, it’s pretty and used as a fuel source for exotic Weapons and reckless magicians. A plasmic core can be cracked open and huffed by a wizard in place of spending Stamina on a Spell. However, if an Oops! Table roll is called for the wizard has overdosed and drops dead, foaming at the mouth.
-Mu3M6bFyZNB1Q5Nrjn0.name: Plasmic Core

-Mu3MHAPMWlA_X11bpdR.description: The Velare, when inactive, looks like an ornate piece of costume jewellery, usually a brooch or a circlet. When active it produces a full body disguise on the wearer formed from hard-light. Grants +4 Disguise. Lasts for 24 hours before needing to be recharged with a plasmic core.
-Mu3MHAPMWlA_X11bpdR.name: Velare

-MXPJTdAZstMAaycOoER.description: Parchment, inks and brushes. A running chronicle of the adventures of Sir Gary and the many victories of Kevin the Monkey Wrangler.
-MXPJTdAZstMAaycOoER.name: Writing Equipment

-MXPLX2ZCuV2A_hAlxcc.description: A blunt weapon? A large astronomical tool? Why not both!
-MXPLX2ZCuV2A_hAlxcc.name: Mace (Large Astrolabe)

-MXPR36QCbFxHm6OGZdJ.description: A football-sized bug that curls up in your backpack, but can be woken once per day to eat its own size in organic matter, no matter how inedible.
-MXPR36QCbFxHm6OGZdJ.name: Devourer

-MXPRJ0o-uP9T8gmTJQ6.description: A floating mass of swirling colours the size of a penny. It follows your every command and leaves a multicolour trail across any surface it touches. Cannot physically interact in any other way.
-MXPRJ0o-uP9T8gmTJQ6.name: Tiny Phantasm

-MerHNwf6v9bFcSdz474.description: Plasmic cores are crystalised starlight cast in metal. Or astral vapours captured in glass. Or maybe hard-ghosts? Whatever it is, it’s pretty and used as a fuel source for exotic Weapons and reckless magicians. A plasmic core can be cracked open and huffed by a wizard in place of spending Stamina on a Spell. -MerHNwf6v9bFcSdz474.name: Plasmic Core

-Merk112ew6s4J1R5Wza.description: Extract the consciousness of a pacified or willing being to be stored within. The consciousness can be injected into the still warm body of a dead being, giving them a new body to inhabit.
-Merk112ew6s4J1R5Wza.name: Essence Extractor

-Mu3nYT8YTXk3WK6bK1_.description: So many lives lost, so many companions torn asunder, in the accidental quest to gather these tomes of esoteric, mystical writings. What do they do? Whence do they come? What will happen if all 5 Volumes are united? Fuck if I know!
-Mu3nYT8YTXk3WK6bK1_.name: 3/5 Volumes of The Pentateuch of the Cosmogony

-MvBow7h4bQCsDkhw1_5.description:
Responds to verbal commands
Can extend/retract, stiffen/loosen, tie/untie, etc.
-MvBow7h4bQCsDkhw1_5.name: Living Rope

-MvBqrEQLXsMfjzMATYR.description:
Bright pink balls. 
Consume to become bouncy and rubbery for 5 minutes.
Immune to falling and impact damage
Can stretch to up to double normal length
Delicate or precise tasks are impossible
-MvBqrEQLXsMfjzMATYR.name: Rubbergum Seed

-MwK7F6rEeMpa62fePty.description: Provides protection against mental assault / influence for 24 hours.
-MwK7F6rEeMpa62fePty.name: Potato from the Great Tuber

-MXPPWLUDvlNmtLYsps2.description:
Flask of oil has charges
in rucksack
-MXPPWLUDvlNmtLYsps2.name: Lantern

-MgYIhwFoJ6zy12lyEJq.description: In rucksack A boon from the Duke de Corticus: A new canvas that does not fall apart in the rain. = full body disguise +4 disguise skill up to 24 hours. Recharge with a plasmic core.
-MgYIhwFoJ6zy12lyEJq.name: Bellare (disguise thorn)

-MgYZVLzxRhSFRxQUw4o.description: Silver is the star metal, the most untouched material fallen from the hump-backed sky. Weapons made from it may inflict Damage to creatures normally immune to material harm.
-MgYZVLzxRhSFRxQUw4o.name: Silver

-MZd-aiKHi94Wz8a--8h.description: The star maps of Corda hold the secrets of travel between the spheres. Every juncture in space and time can be found on its many square metred face if one is sufficiently educated in its use. Test Astrology to tell the precise destination of any portal.

-MZ_J0nYxYGrOY5QSUC4.name: Tea Set

-MZbHzW4dyFfabGJum5S.description: This throwing disc is designed to play sports with but can also be used as a weapon (damage as club)
-MZbHzW4dyFfabGJum5S.name: Frisbee

-MT47l6s7hT91k0CvGZQ.description: Requires twenty minutes to set up and use but doesn’t need to be outside. Consists of a ruby specular, charms against reciprocal observation, and complicated charts of the spheres. Grants +1 to Astrology.
-MT47l6s7hT91k0CvGZQ.name: Astrological Equipment

-MT8Ato9fKXegSyobg4O.description: And here is the description of the skill.
-MT8Ato9fKXegSyobg4O.name: Here is a Skill

-MT8Avodx98MydGl5V-A.description:
If true, the text will not wrap, but instead will truncate with a text overflow ellipsis.
Note that text overflow can only happen with block or inline-block level elements (the element needs to have a width in order to overflow).
-MT8Avodx98MydGl5V-A.name: Test 2

-MTBTIUs-ZKVDHV2yc8D.description: This includes any Skill you might think of that comes under the heading of arts and crafts. Blacksmithing, carpentry, painting, opera singing, anything like that. Roll Under the Skill if you want to do something that knowledge of this Skill would reasonably cover. A carpenter might be able to spot a weak bridge while a blacksmith could shoe a horse or an opera singer could identify an aria. Be flexible and reasonable.
-MTBTIUs-ZKVDHV2yc8D.name: Crafting Skills

-MXO5oAQfXFAX06FqKZM.description:
The mischievous apprentice’s favourite Spell, Jolt sends an arc of electricity from the wizard’s outstretched hand towards a target. Ignores Armour. 

Damage:

1-2: 2
3-4: 3
5: 5
6: 7
7+: 9
-MXO5oAQfXFAX06FqKZM.name: Jolt

-MXPzOL69tpnB7FvYucC.description: Use of this allows the detection of magic. On a successful Test you focus your inner eye and all sorcerous activity glows faintly for a moment.
-MXPzOL69tpnB7FvYucC.name: Second Sight

-MXNzEQHC3NDok8rCTrH.description: The wizard or a target of their choosing may travel to any location within a single sphere instantly. If unfamiliar with the location they must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or be thrown wildly off course to potentially devastating results.
-MXNzEQHC3NDok8rCTrH.name: Teleport

-MXNzPDgf59ckcxmU4cS.description: The usefulness of the ability to clamber up things cannot be overstated. Most climbs should be single rolls though longer or more difficult climbs may require multiple rolls. On these climbs consider requiring a number or total or repeated failures to fall off unless it is a particularly  merciless ascent. The GM should use their discretion.
-MXNzPDgf59ckcxmU4cS.name: Climb

-MXNzcA_4R-y2aLzvcdO.description: The wizard or a target of their choosing may travel to any location within a single sphere instantly. If unfamiliar with the location they must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or be thrown wildly off course to potentially devastating results.
-MXNzcA_4R-y2aLzvcdO.name: Teleport

-MXNexQihmfVdb5OIQmJ.description: Anything worth having is well hidden so one must look very carefully. Use this to spot traps, things normally hidden, or things out of the ordinary.
-MXNexQihmfVdb5OIQmJ.name: Awareness

-MXNexQqiVjF4RWT-4-8.description: The usefulness of the ability to clamber up things cannot be overstated. Most climbs should be single rolls though longer or more difficult climbs may require multiple rolls. On these climbs consider requiring a number or total or repeated failures to fall off unless it is a particularly  merciless ascent. The GM should use their discretion.
-MXNexQqiVjF4RWT-4-8.name: Climb

-MXO2NzmJtdq5E8dxepH.description: The wizard or a target of their choosing may travel to any location within a single sphere instantly. If unfamiliar with the location they must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or be thrown wildly off course to potentially devastating results.
-MXO2NzmJtdq5E8dxepH.name: Teleport

-MZ4YSY6xNR5g1FtqGmH.description: The wizard speaks nonsense while watching the intended target, causing their words to trip and confuse. This may be done under their breath and relatively subtly.
-MZ4YSY6xNR5g1FtqGmH.name: Babble

-MZ4YSYj_Nov92i_K-jY.description: The wizard explains, clearly, sternly, why it is impossible that the spirit could be here at this time. The spirit must Test its Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or be sent to somewhere less improbable.
-MZ4YSYj_Nov92i_K-jY.name: Banish Spirit

-MZ4YSZHxHOFtxOvtST5.description: A wizard’s touch can shake up someone’s mind like a snow globe. The target makes all rolls at a -1 penalty until their head clears. Lasts for 3 minutes.
-MZ4YSZHxHOFtxOvtST5.name: Befuddle

-Mu3OeEw9TGIFHOHwk0E.description: Test this to navigate between the stars on a ship with golden mirror sails.
-Mu3OeEw9TGIFHOHwk0E.name: Golden Barge Pilot

-Mu3PFGhuG7cJ0xo_goL.description: The wizard hikes up their wizard robe and stomps their wizard feet. An area 30 metres around them suffers a massive earthquake. Everyone must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or fall through a crack in the earth, taking falling Damage and being stuck in a bloody great big hole (7.8.1). Buildings may be wrecked unless especially sturdy.
-Mu3PFGhuG7cJ0xo_goL.name: Earthquake

-Mu3PIz-6ypWg3J0VQhK.description: The wizard claps neatly and issues forth the light of a thousand suns from their hands. All within 20 metres must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or be blinded for 1d6 minutes.
-Mu3PIz-6ypWg3J0VQhK.name: Flash

-Mu3PLa34-D7mOLq6gVI.description: A simple but effective summoning of fire. Flames the size of a small bonfire appear somewhere within 12 metres of the wizard. Once present there is no accounting for its actions. Exchange
-Mu3PLa34-D7mOLq6gVI.name: Ember

-MXPIkjfOZX696H24XKZ.description: Use this to gain insight into angles, pressures, numbers, and other such arcane arts. You could, for instance, Test your Mathmology to get a good idea of the surface tension of a ball of inert plasmic goo or to find the fulcrum for tripping a giant.
-MXPIkjfOZX696H24XKZ.name: Mathmology

-MXPInvA7BOyjDfmL5P_.description: An essential Skill for anyone intent on travelling the stars. Can be used to identify stars and constellations, to gather hints on the destination of interdimensional portals, and to make star charts.
-MXPInvA7BOyjDfmL5P_.name: Astrology

-MXPIrJAC3XAkFQLOnC4.description: Anything worth having is well hidden so one must look very carefully. Use this to spot traps, things normally hidden, or things out of the ordinary.
-MXPIrJAC3XAkFQLOnC4.name: Awareness

-MXPIz9fW4pBPdyuoY_7.description: When wizards lose their glasses they mumble to themselves until they turn up. The thing being sought must be a specific object, not a general category or type, and the direction is only given in terms of compass points.
-MXPIz9fW4pBPdyuoY_7.name: Find

-MXPJ1PgIPhroVmJfCEt.description: Test this to get an idea of how much something is worth.
-MXPJ1PgIPhroVmJfCEt.name: Evaluate

-MXPJ3wZusiPmUECwqUk.description: Used to identify marks, handshakes, code words, etc. of one specific society. You would, for example, be able to read the secret marks left on people’s door posts by fellow hobos.
-MXPJ3wZusiPmUECwqUk.name: Secret Signs

-MgYWO2SV6UK0LImDJuH.description: A simple but effective summoning of fire. Flames the size of a small bonfire appear somewhere within 12 metres of the wizard. Once present there is no accounting for its actions. Exchange
-MgYWO2SV6UK0LImDJuH.name: Ember

-MgYZlGDwYPX02sebxvU.description: Fighting with a big ol' mace.
-MgYZlGDwYPX02sebxvU.name: Mace

On these climbs consider requiring a number or total or repeated failures to fall off unless it is a particularly  merciless ascent. The GM should use their discretion.
-MwJsJPj-oh_eM67FrIR.name: Climb

-MXPQfioaNmSbW2Yqr5e.description: Choose what general category of Weapons this covers when you take this Skill. Roll Versus during combat when using the appropriate method of assault. The GM is encouraged to allow Weapon categories to be broadly applicable, such as Glaive Fighting being equivalent to Polearm Fighting.
-MXPQfioaNmSbW2Yqr5e.name: Weapon Fighting (sword cane)

-MXPRGWdEwtcG0wMOcsW.description: This Spell prevents the wizard from getting rained upon for one shower.
-MXPRGWdEwtcG0wMOcsW.name: Protection from Rain

-MXPRL1DHhrFYNwHgT4H.description: The Wizard-Knights are most famous for their remote combat whereby they swing their Silver Swords seemingly at nothing only for their opponents, many metres away, to be torn to tatters. This Spell can be used in place of a melee attack by Rolling Versus as normal and inflicting Damage according to the Weapon used. May only be used against targets within clear sight.
-MXPRL1DHhrFYNwHgT4H.name: Callous Strike

-MXPRRqlCkFwILcwLfPT.description: Snuff a small flame with the wave of a hand.
-MXPRRqlCkFwILcwLfPT.name: Quench

-MXPRd9JlLlSFwp_5lRA.description: The wizard focuses their sight on the unambiguous truth of matter, enabling them to see through illusions for the next 10 minutes.
-MXPRd9JlLlSFwp_5lRA.name: True Seeing

-MXPRd9PqRPa28YIoxS_.description: Covers the use of props to change your appearance. When in disguise you must Roll Under this when someone is liable to see through it. Opposed by Awareness when under scrutiny.
-MXPRd9PqRPa28YIoxS_.name: Disguise

-MXPRd9WKuOCvDIKVkh6.description: Use of this allows the detection of magic. On a successful Test you focus your inner eye and all sorcerous activity glows faintly for a moment.
-MXPRd9WKuOCvDIKVkh6.name: Second Sight

-MXPRd9fDC2jSqDOB3yl.description: Used to stitch wounds and apply ointments, stop bleeding, slow poison and the like. Also used for stabilising dying people.
-MXPRd9fDC2jSqDOB3yl.name: Healing

-MXPRd9setQ5dnrvUakY.description: The wizard disentangles a Spell from this instance of reality. To do so they must Roll Versus the original casting if disentanglement is possible at all. (Double cost of original spell)
-MXPRd9setQ5dnrvUakY.name: Undo

-MXPRqqsUSIiFHDVPCLu.description:
The wizard may wildly gesticulate at a brittle object no larger than an 
umbrella and cause it to shatter into a million pieces. Living targets may 
Test their Luck to avoid this unpleasant Spell
-MXPRqqsUSIiFHDVPCLu.name: Shatter

-MgYZjaaSUDz3dikOXl7.description: Choose what general category of Weapons this covers when you take this Skill. Roll Versus during combat when using the appropriate method of assault. The GM is encouraged to allow Weapon categories to be broadly applicable, such as Glaive Fighting being equivalent to Polearm Fighting.
-MgYZjaaSUDz3dikOXl7.name: Weapon Fighting

-MZ9IZb78O86dKkpUdT5.description: Used for rolling, balancing, falling, jumping, etc.
-MZ9IZb78O86dKkpUdT5.name: Acrobatics

-MZL9_iPD4xw4VDNHWjh.description: Cause a target’s lungs to fill with water. They must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies). If they fail they start to Drown (7.9) and are incapacitated as water pours from their mouth. They may Test again once per Turn until they pass, at which point the Spell ends.
-MZL9_iPD4xw4VDNHWjh.name: Drown

-MZL9hVsZSAEbKuhSE0l.description: Use this while swimming in dangerous waters, diving, holding your breath for long periods, and so on. If you have this Skill you don’t need to roll it for normal conditions. Characters without it are assumed to not be able to swim and need to test Swimming every round they remain in the water or start Drowning (7.9). Receive a penalty to this Skill equal to half the number of item slots filled.
-MZL9hVsZSAEbKuhSE0l.name: Swim

-MZL9hW-D3QkcOjn3qB7.description: Beware! If a wizard screws their nose and twists their fingers at you then a Tongue Twister is coming your way. The target must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or have their tongue literally tied in knots. This requires some time and a fair bit of patience to disentangle.
-MZL9hW-D3QkcOjn3qB7.name: Tongue Twister

-MZL9hW1MVeGlZI7mSVa.description: The wizard disentangles a Spell from this instance of reality. To do so they must Roll Versus the original casting if disentanglement is possible at all. (Double cost of original spell)
-MZL9hW1MVeGlZI7mSVa.name: Undo

-MZL9hW2UUFHqOD3TukE.description: Whether this is opening a portal to the plane of slime or channelling the sprites of sickness, all can agree that it is quite disgusting. The wizard blows forth the “web” from their nose and all in a cone extending 12 metres in front of the wizard are trapped unless they Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies). Each Turn anything passing through or out of it must repeat the Test or become stuck. Dries up after 12 rounds.
-MZL9hW2UUFHqOD3TukE.name: Web

-MZL9hW4Sskqg9lj_qM_.description: The art of remaining unseen. This is Tested only when someone or something is actively trying to detect you. The sneaker would Roll Versus the Awareness of those searching for them; anyone beating the sneaker’s score detects them.
-MZL9hW4Sskqg9lj_qM_.name: Sneak

-MZL9hW5ph4CPbD2g394.description: Use of this allows the detection of magic. On a successful Test you focus your inner eye and all sorcerous activity glows faintly for a moment.
-MZL9hW5ph4CPbD2g394.name: Second Sight

-MZ_yifIcnbgneuj4Yt7.description: You snap a twig or other brittle object to cause an injury in another. They must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or suffer a broken bone.
-MZ_yifIcnbgneuj4Yt7.name: Brittle Twigs

-MZbGm9Q8IFkJQU1Wch_.description: Throw a Frisbee at an enemy as a ranged attack, defend against attacks made with Frisbees or play Frisbee or disc golf
-MZbGm9Q8IFkJQU1Wch_.name: FRISBEE

-MZbXYtSkwWLnO8A4kQD.description: Cause a subject to be fixed in place. While they are so held they do not move, breathe, fall, perspire, acquire, or otherwise change. They are totally immune to harm, in fact. Lasts for 3 minutes.
-MZbXYtSkwWLnO8A4kQD.name: Affix

-MZbXYtmtKIR8WCBMcEz.description: Cause inanimate objects to question their place. One object up to the size of a human baby may be caused to hop around and do whatever else the wizard wishes.
-MZbXYtmtKIR8WCBMcEz.name: Animate

-MZbXiOsyzIMOfBsZhvv.description: The wizard undergoes a distressing transformation into an inanimate object no larger than a piano and no smaller than a cup. Lasts until ended.
-MZbXiOsyzIMOfBsZhvv.name: Assume Shape

-MZbXiPFYUPNoFxFpyzf.description: Elevates the wizard or another on the backs of tiny invisible sprites who answer only to their summoner. May float about for 3 minutes.
-MZbXiPFYUPNoFxFpyzf.name: Levitate

-MZcWRYqYOtbZtV9VmXX.description: An essential Skill for anyone intent on travelling the stars. Can be used to identify stars and constellations, to gather hints on the destination of interdimensional portals, and to make star charts.
-MZcWRYqYOtbZtV9VmXX.name: Astrology

-MZbZwSjJjSPRRZS_Inq.description: The Red Priests posit that all negative behaviour is a symptom of some level of possession, or at least direct influence, by the forces of Change, unwitting agents of Mass in need of healing. The wizard throws salt at their target and Rolls Versus the possessing spirit to cast it out. In the case of a Fumble the spirit is drawn into and possesses the wizard.
-MZbZwSjJjSPRRZS_Inq.name: Exorcism

-MZbZwTFLNEXurSDWlGE.description: The wizard forms a mouth with their hands through which they can speak any language. They can simultaneously cup their other hand to their ear to understand them in return. Lasts for one conversation.
-MZbZwTFLNEXurSDWlGE.name: Languages

-MZbZwTgR2gz0c4-VWm6.description: The wizard speaks nonsense while watching the intended target, causing their words to trip and confuse. This may be done under their breath and relatively subtly.
-MZbZwTgR2gz0c4-VWm6.name: Babble

-MZbZwU0Acdnxnd_WyKg.description: In the eyes of one poor target the wizard grows into a primal monster from the depths of their lizard brain. They will attempt to flee and if flight is impossible they will curl up in a ball and whimper. They may Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) to resist the illusion.
-MZbZwU0Acdnxnd_WyKg.name: Fear

-MZb_9QlzmKA6rR3iKG_.description: Use Fly much as you would Run. In normal situations this doesn’t need testing, only in chases or high winds, maybe. Anyone attempting to Fly without this Skill must Test every Round to make sure they don’t crash or lose control.
-MZb_9QlzmKA6rR3iKG_.name: Fly

-MZbfAVZ26RS-dVq7TvP.description: A wizard’s touch can shake up someone’s mind like a snow globe. The target makes all rolls at a -1 penalty until their head clears. Lasts for 3 minutes.
-MZbfAVZ26RS-dVq7TvP.name: Befuddle

-MZbfAWHfxHKLouqXabq.description: You snap a twig or other brittle object to cause an injury in another. They must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or suffer a broken bone.
-MZbfAWHfxHKLouqXabq.name: Brittle Twigs

-MZbfAX-tEbJC_t9CvIk.description: Cause an item to grow half its size again if it fails to Test its Luck (or Skill for Enemies). Lasts for 3 minutes
-MZbfAX-tEbJC_t9CvIk.name: Grow

-MZbfAX_HqNTaUfmIBLV.description: The wizard can get the answer to one question from the entrails of a living creature. The size and importance of the creature influences the level of knowledge gained. Small, common animals are able to offer yes or no answers, oxen can predict things obtusely, lamassu may offer explicit and thorough advice.
-MZbfAX_HqNTaUfmIBLV.name: Read Entrails

-MZlDq9k54lVt3vXNyTd.description: When making a good impression is important Roll Versus your host’s Etiquette. Represents a mechanical understanding of social conduct and those who are better at it are more discerning.
-MZlDq9k54lVt3vXNyTd.name: Etiquette

-MZbt1rZOnauGRoLFzFw.description:

-MZmiPxKQJWsm5t-Tgjk.name: Tracking

-MZmiW9pi3XKTm01qkGm.description: Covers the use of props to change your appearance. When in disguise you must Roll Under this when someone is liable to see through it. Opposed by Awareness when under scrutiny.

-MZmj5hw7syyi0olbQeX.description: When making a good impression is important Roll Versus your host’s Etiquette. Represents a mechanical understanding of social conduct and those who are better at it are more discerning.

-MdB1qASE4672YHrFaBf.name: Light

-Mqm19tU2T8q9qlnqXRZ.description: When wizards lose their glasses they mumble to themselves until they turn up. The thing being sought must be a specific object, not a general category or type, and the direction is only given in terms of compass points.

-MbU7wU7nPaiNPx8JjZI.description: Use this to set and disarm traps. When setting traps Roll Under your Trapping Skill and describe how the trap is made with the materials at hand. When someone wishes to disarm a trap they must Roll Versus the original trap-setter’s Trapping Skill. If the GM doesn’t know what that number should be assume 6 to be pretty simple while 12 is incredibly hard. Scale it between those as appropriate.
-MbU7wU7nPaiNPx8JjZI.name: Trapping

-MbU84M6kEo1e-7CMsjG.description: The wizard chooses a reality wherein the lock was open all along. May be used to open any mundane door or container and counteract a Lock Spell.
-MbU84M6kEo1e-7CMsjG.name: Open

-MbU8Irq-bu95xgAlxGp.description: The wizard rubs a surface vigorously, making it translucent. Can penetrate up to 12 inches of material. Lead and Silver are immune
-MbU8Irq-bu95xgAlxGp.name: See Through

-MbU9zZiqZyZPWNBPxCR.description: Magically lock an object. The object must have a lockable aspect to it but is now magically sealed. Permanent until undone or dismissed.

Nothing may pass without the wizard’s permission (it is recommended that they remember to allow air). Lasts for 12 minutes.
-Mg5_-EixDL4-v3kDHDm.name: Wall of Power

-MqmVkzP21SS4ZLAp4kq.description: Used for rolling, balancing, falling, jumping, etc.

-MgV7ZGnHSfmvH0vPuL5.description: Use this to gain insight into angles, pressures, numbers, and other such arcane arts. You could, for instance, Test your Mathmology to get a good idea of the surface tension of a ball of inert plasmic goo or to find the fulcrum for tripping a giant.
-MgV7ZGnHSfmvH0vPuL5.name: Mathmology
