-MhwmQGtR-vq_maC2LGX.name: Ward

-MhwmZb-iKMEQ58va-k5.description: Use this while swimming in dangerous waters, diving, holding your breath for long periods, and so on. If you have this Skill you don’t need to roll it for normal conditions. Characters without it are assumed to not be able to swim and need to test Swimming every round they remain in the water or start Drowning (7.9). Receive a penalty to this Skill equal to half the number of item slots filled.
-MhwmZb-iKMEQ58va-k5.name: Swim

-Mhwmbkz5EL53YkLPGP6.description: Anything worth having is well hidden so one must look very carefully. Use this to spot traps, things normally hidden, or things out of the ordinary.
-Mhwmbkz5EL53YkLPGP6.name: Awareness

-MhwmeQ_C4lLXPyLl8jS.description: An essential Skill for anyone intent on travelling the stars. Can be used to identify stars and constellations, to gather hints on the destination of interdimensional portals, and to make star charts.
-MhwmeQ_C4lLXPyLl8jS.name: Astrology

-MhwnmlctJ_pZq1BOLzR.description: Anything worth having is well hidden so one must look very carefully. Use this to spot traps, things normally hidden, or things out of the ordinary.
-MhwnmlctJ_pZq1BOLzR.name: Awareness

-MhwnpkeMxadbS7JHmEK.description: Covers the use of props to change your appearance. When in disguise you must Roll Under this when someone is liable to see through it. Opposed by Awareness when under scrutiny.
-MhwnpkeMxadbS7JHmEK.name: Disguise

-MhwnxOi45WH4TXHcEyr.description: When making a good impression is important Roll Versus your host’s Etiquette. Represents a mechanical understanding of social conduct and those who are better at it are more discerning.
-MhwnxOi45WH4TXHcEyr.name: Etiquette

-MhwnxOmk1EO4lelmQ31.description: The necromancer must place their hands on a living subject and allow their fingertips to transform into sucking apertures which drain the victim of blood. Deal 2d6 Damage to your victim and regain half as much Stamina.
-MhwnxOmk1EO4lelmQ31.name: Leech

-Mhwo2HNA7oTVp3gGIO-.description: Used for lifting and breaking things. May also be used to grapple people if no grappling-appropriate Weapon Skill is possessed, though it counts for half rounded up.
-Mhwo2HNA7oTVp3gGIO-.name: Strength

-MhwvcIL9M3lEpz2wp2r.description: Anything worth having is well hidden so one must look very carefully. Use this to spot traps, things normally hidden, or things out of the ordinary.
-MhwvcIL9M3lEpz2wp2r.name: Awareness

-Mhwvcu4F4Qsi26OKcFX.description: I used to make stamps; out of rubber, out of potatoes, out of wood. Whatever works I can carve and make very pretty stamps.
-Mhwvcu4F4Qsi26OKcFX.name: Crafting skill - Stamp maker

-MhwwUIl5hnigU9oZnFl.description: When it matters how fast you are, or if you can reach somewhere in time, use this. A basic chase is an Roll Versus.
-MhwwUIl5hnigU9oZnFl.name: Run

-MhwpzpcJrK752CSr214.description: Anything worth having is well hidden so one must look very carefully. Use this to spot traps, things normally hidden, or things out of the ordinary.
-MhwpzpcJrK752CSr214.name: Awareness

-MhwqAZavv8vk2Bf2_R8.description: Used for lifting and breaking things. May also be used to grapple people if no grappling-appropriate Weapon Skill is possessed, though it counts for half rounded up.
-MhwqAZavv8vk2Bf2_R8.name: Strength

-MhwqtJX3ob141Di5gA2.description: everyone knows what a gun is
-MhwqtJX3ob141Di5gA2.name: pistol fighting

-Mi1AYt_BmldltleHgrt.description: When making a good impression is important Roll Versus your host’s Etiquette. Represents a mechanical understanding of social conduct and those who are better at it are more discerning.
-Mi1AYt_BmldltleHgrt.name: Etiquette

-Mi1Alp2xRn3DclNAGyH.description: Open up the mind to universal love and cause two subjects to Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or cease hostilities. They will still defend themselves if attacked but will at least appreciate the pettiness of it.
-Mi1Alp2xRn3DclNAGyH.name: Peace

-Mi1AlpAS7CV9TAdH-1W.description: The recipient’s eyes glow purple as they experience an alternative reality where people are kind, their surroundings are beautiful, their food is indulgent, and so on. This doesn’t change the reality of things but it does make them more palatable. Lasts until they want it to end.
-Mi1AlpAS7CV9TAdH-1W.name: Purple Lens

-Mi1AlpHKoG7vFIiWTjT.description: This Spell prevents the wizard from getting rained upon for one shower.
-Mi1AlpHKoG7vFIiWTjT.name: Protection from Rain

-Ml2sNLUM95S2XWyS4OZ.description: When it matters how fast you are, or if you can reach somewhere in time, use this. A basic chase is an Roll Versus.
-Ml2sNLUM95S2XWyS4OZ.name: Run

-MnwreslYQ7nAnEJIk8E.description: Choose what general category of Weapons this covers when you take this Skill. Roll Versus during combat when using the appropriate method of assault. The GM is encouraged to allow Weapon categories to be broadly applicable, such as Glaive Fighting being equivalent to Polearm Fighting.
-MnwreslYQ7nAnEJIk8E.name: Unarmed

-MnwrpVwkhGf03ntUA0k.description: Use this to set and disarm traps. When setting traps Roll Under your Trapping Skill and describe how the trap is made with the materials at hand. When someone wishes to disarm a trap they must Roll Versus the original trap-setter’s Trapping Skill. If the GM doesn’t know what that number should be assume 6 to be pretty simple while 12 is incredibly hard. Scale it between those as appropriate.
-MnwrpVwkhGf03ntUA0k.name: Trapping

-Mnwrs2nvbU4mL1o-FFN.description: You may use this Skill in place of your Weapon Skill while fighting in confined spaces where you would otherwise be unable to swing your Weapon about. You ignore all penalties the GM might associate with fighting in such a situation.
-Mnwrs2nvbU4mL1o-FFN.name: Tunnel Fighting

-Mnwru7qO90Rn7YSFuFi.description: When making a good impression is important Roll Versus your host’s Etiquette. Represents a mechanical understanding of social conduct and those who are better at it are more discerning.
-Mnwru7qO90Rn7YSFuFi.name: Etiquette

-Mnws1V8HjiPTSfb7ncU.description: Choose what general category of Weapons this covers when you take this Skill. Roll Versus during combat when using the appropriate method of assault. The GM is encouraged to allow Weapon categories to be broadly applicable, such as Glaive Fighting being equivalent to Polearm Fighting.
-Mnws1V8HjiPTSfb7ncU.name: Pistolet

-Mqb8VoWLJvihuLVeSwA.description: Used for lifting and breaking things. May also be used to grapple people if no grappling-appropriate Weapon Skill is possessed, though it counts for half rounded up.
-Mqb8VoWLJvihuLVeSwA.name: Strength

-Mqb8ZlMEY6x9nUESQU0.description: Use this to set and disarm traps. When setting traps Roll Under your Trapping Skill and describe how the trap is made with the materials at hand. When someone wishes to disarm a trap they must Roll Versus the original trap-setter’s Trapping Skill. If the GM doesn’t know what that number should be assume 6 to be pretty simple while 12 is incredibly hard. Scale it between those as appropriate.
-Mqb8ZlMEY6x9nUESQU0.name: Trapping

-Mqb8cBrvq86pIOUXTIo.description: The wizard chooses a reality wherein the lock was open all along. May be used to open any mundane door or container and counteract a Lock Spell.
-Mqb8cBrvq86pIOUXTIo.name: Open

-Mqb8g3-Dt2fST7EyPrJ.description: The wizard rubs a surface vigorously, making it translucent. Can penetrate up to 12 inches of material. Lead and Silver are immune
-Mqb8g3-Dt2fST7EyPrJ.name: See Through

-Mqb8uGPTxPuytX-9eqY.description: Magically lock an object. The object must have a lockable aspect to it but is now magically sealed. Permanent until undone or dismissed.
-Mqb8uGPTxPuytX-9eqY.name: Lock

-MvBrUL-nPzViizixLdw.description: The usefulness of the ability to clamber up things cannot be overstated. Most climbs should be single rolls though longer or more difficult climbs may require multiple rolls. On these climbs consider requiring a number or total or repeated failures to fall off unless it is a particularly  merciless ascent. The GM should use their discretion.
-MvBrUL-nPzViizixLdw.name: Climb (only with claws)

-Mu3VHCW77dmQO5L48G5.description: An essential Skill for anyone intent on travelling the stars. Can be used to identify stars and constellations, to gather hints on the destination of interdimensional portals, and to make star charts.
-Mu3VHCW77dmQO5L48G5.name: Astrology

-Mu3Vc1a2FjjMrvbAxcp.description: Use of this allows the detection of magic. On a successful Test you focus your inner eye and all sorcerous activity glows faintly for a moment.
-Mu3Vc1a2FjjMrvbAxcp.name: Second Sight

-Mu3Vjx7W_zJZP-1e-YM.description: The wizard hikes up their wizard robe and stomps their wizard feet. An area 30 metres around them suffers a massive earthquake. Everyone must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or fall through a crack in the earth, taking falling Damage and being stuck in a bloody great big hole (7.8.1). Buildings may be wrecked unless especially sturdy.
-Mu3Vjx7W_zJZP-1e-YM.name: Earthquake

-Mu3VmYCbtqlZy38Rkps.description: The wizard claps neatly and issues forth the light of a thousand suns from their hands. All within 20 metres must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or be blinded for 1d6 minutes.
-Mu3VmYCbtqlZy38Rkps.name: Flash

-Mu3VozXLyDl9BTbwQTn.description: A simple but effective summoning of fire. Flames the size of a small bonfire appear somewhere within 12 metres of the wizard. Once present there is no accounting for its actions. Exchange
-Mu3VozXLyDl9BTbwQTn.name: Ember

-Mu3yK_xCFL1f5utHdTF.description: Test this to navigate between the stars on a ship with golden mirror sails.
-Mu3yK_xCFL1f5utHdTF.name: Golden Barge Pilot

-Mu43t2nxM81IyjxYJi7.description: Used to stitch wounds and apply ointments, stop bleeding, slow poison and the like. Also used for stabilising dying people.
-Mu43t2nxM81IyjxYJi7.name: Healing

-Mu44D_jJR2ezjtHEKH6.description:
Necromancers, known for their social inadequacy, often find themselves having to make friends. This Spell requires a fresh, or at least whole and lubricated, corpse. The wizard rolls 2d6 plus their Posthumous Vitality Skill Total and consults the following chart (13+ counts for an Advancement tick): 

4-12 Nothing happens. 
13-14 The vitality is clumsily applied, causing the body to explode messily. A new one will need to be found. 
15-16 The creature is animated and will last for 24 hours before literally falling to pieces. 
17+ Perfect reanimation. The creature will last until destroyed.
-Mu44D_jJR2ezjtHEKH6.name: Posthumous Vitality

-Mu44GSZTlQErpN1huT_.description: Necromancers often talk to skulls. Sometimes they talk back. Use of this Spell enables speaking with the dead, who answer one question per casting. Requires a skull.
-Mu44GSZTlQErpN1huT_.name: Skeletal Counsel

-Mu44KRbn92hqA5uAmQR.description: Those who study the dead consider it necessary to develop a profound sympathy with their subject — how can you speak with the dead if you don’t understand the dead? Torpor helps build post-mortem empathy by causing the necromancer to temporarily die. Bodily functions are halted, no food, water, or air is needed, and they are, by most vulgar definitions of the word, dead. The Spell lasts until ended by the wizard, who remains vaguely aware of their surroundings to the extent of being conscious of sound and movement but not of what is said or who is saying it. They will still take Damage from bodily abuse while under the effect and can indeed become irretrievably dead
-Mu44KRbn92hqA5uAmQR.name: Torpor

-Mu44Mtn5bKA32DMYiWK.description: The art of remaining unseen. This is Tested only when someone or something is actively trying to detect you. The sneaker would Roll Versus the Awareness of those searching for them; anyone beating the sneaker’s score detects them.
-Mu44Mtn5bKA32DMYiWK.name: Sneak

-MvC5nwak_PlMvOuWF7z.description: The usefulness of the ability to clamber up things cannot be overstated. Most climbs should be single rolls though longer or more difficult climbs may require multiple rolls. On these climbs consider requiring a number or total or repeated failures to fall off unless it is a particularly  merciless ascent. The GM should use their discretion.
-MvC5nwak_PlMvOuWF7z.name: Climb

-MvGV2LkZAvUyPmUhqLE.description: The wizard speaks nonsense while watching the intended target, causing their words to trip and confuse. This may be done under their breath and relatively subtly.
-MvGV2LkZAvUyPmUhqLE.name: Babble

-MwNryuqLDwO48hF9YgK.description: Used for rolling, balancing, falling, jumping, etc.
-MwNryuqLDwO48hF9YgK.name: Acrobatics

-MSnwsMLBAJkg3CrKAbw.description: A bale hook counts as a Knife for Damage and grants +1 on rolls to lift heavy objects.
-MSnwsMLBAJkg3CrKAbw.name: Bale Hook

-MSnx6tPr01CUflrMLHt.description: The star maps of Corda hold the secrets of travel between the spheres. Every juncture in space and time can be found on its many square metred face if one is sufficiently educated in its use. Test Astrology to tell the precise destination of any portal.
-MSnx6tPr01CUflrMLHt.name: Blue Star maps of Corda

-MSnxGa-Ksf4jb-05qTa.description: An Epopt’s Staff is a tool, an advert, and, in a pinch, a Weapon. In its head is set a cloudy ruby, like a useless magnifying glass, which grants the user +1 Second Sight while peering through it.
-MSnxGa-Ksf4jb-05qTa.name: Epopt's Staff

-MSnxUyvM58_yvRzUZu7.description: A fusil is a long Weapon that looks like a rifle and can be used in melee as a Club. A Fusil holds 6 charges before the plasmic core needs replacing.
-MSnxUyvM58_yvRzUZu7.name: Fusil (Ranged)

-MSnxgVM8W834_jxE_ag.description: A Fusil can also be used as a club.
-MSnxgVM8W834_jxE_ag.name: Fusil (Melee)

-MSnxl2x-SyvW2ir0sI9.description: Knuckle dice are made from the nimble, petal shaped knuckle bones of goblins and make excellent two sided dice.
-MSnxl2x-SyvW2ir0sI9.name: Knuckle Dice

-MSnxqQGSkj_y6KsyqEk.description: A pistolet is a hand held energy Weapon. Holds enough energy for 8 shots.
-MSnxqQGSkj_y6KsyqEk.name: Pistolet

-MSnxxKLyDUhqJS8Xoet.description: Plasmic cores are crystalised starlight cast in metal. Or astral vapours captured in glass. Or maybe hard-ghosts? Whatever it is, it’s pretty and used as a fuel source for exotic Weapons and reckless magicians. A plasmic core can be cracked open and huffed by a wizard in place of spending Stamina on a Spell. However, if an Oops! Table roll is called for the wizard has overdosed and drops dead, foaming at the mouth.
-MSnxxKLyDUhqJS8Xoet.name: Plasmic Core

-MSny0yElB9py1TIwDwJ.description: The pocket barometer is part of a fashionable affectation for the metropolitan Troikan. Though the city has no discernable weather it is considered polite to check it intermittently and comment on the present clemency and hope for it to continue into the future. Examining its quartz face will inform you of future weather with 5 in 6 accuracy.
-MSny0yElB9py1TIwDwJ.name: Pocket Barometer

-MSny7fUM6FLjTe0rSwc.description: Pocket gods are little cloth puppets made in the image of your numerous gods. If you whisper a secret to one and throw it away you regain 1 Luck.
-MSny7fUM6FLjTe0rSwc.name: Pocket Gods

-MSnyDrunYxyV0wJED0k.description: Ruby lorgnettes are collapsable spectacles made with ruby lenses that require a free hand to use. While wearing them your sight is impaired but you can see sorcerous activity clearly (+2 Second Sight).
-MSnyDrunYxyV0wJED0k.name: Ruby Lorgnettes

-MSnyHKEw87WNH7tAOYC.description: Salt is the poor man’s Silver. Where Silver kills the demonic and the dead Salt merely harms or bars.
-MSnyHKEw87WNH7tAOYC.name: Salt

-MSnyMEX8UfOSUdAwX1x.description: Silver is the star metal, the most untouched material fallen from the hump-backed sky. Weapons made from it may inflict Damage to creatures normally immune to material harm.
-MSnyMEX8UfOSUdAwX1x.name: Silver

-MSnyVgC4vAgAC8sTtfo.description: A tea set grants +1 to Etiquette when you have the time to sit down and make tea for those you are trying to impress.
-MSnyVgC4vAgAC8sTtfo.name: Tea Set

-MSnyc2IE9GP4KK3TvCR.description: The Velare, when inactive, looks like an ornate piece of costume jewellery, usually a brooch or a circlet. When active it produces a full body disguise on the wearer formed from hard-light. Grants +4 Disguise. Lasts for 24 hours before needing to be recharged with a plasmic core.
-MSnyc2IE9GP4KK3TvCR.name: Velare

-MSnyhtYRHyWh4AfPcQi.description: Witch-hair ropes are immune to manipulation via magical means
-MSnyhtYRHyWh4AfPcQi.name: Witch-Hair Rope

-MSnyktqRrOT_UxgjoNT.description: A yoke gives you +4 carry capacity while worn but you can’t use your hands while wearing it.
-MSnyktqRrOT_UxgjoNT.name: Yoke

-MSoCZclB5Yop3IOpEEk.description: Knuckle dice are made from the nimble, petal shaped knuckle bones of goblins and make excellent two sided dice.
-MSoCZclB5Yop3IOpEEk.name: Knuckle Dice

-MSoD-1gYXOUUPtWf3R2.description: Requires twenty minutes to set up and use but doesn’t need to be outside. Consists of a ruby specular, charms against reciprocal observation, and complicated charts of the spheres. Grants +1 to Astrology.
-MSoD-1gYXOUUPtWf3R2.name: Astrological Equipment

-MXNZYBig4fHjKmaXJvW.description: Used for rolling, balancing, falling, jumping, etc.
-MXNZYBig4fHjKmaXJvW.name: Acrobatics

-MXNZ_znS3m2HTFyR-dg.description: An essential Skill for anyone intent on travelling the stars. Can be used to identify stars and constellations, to gather hints on the destination of interdimensional portals, and to make star charts.
-MXNZ_znS3m2HTFyR-dg.name: Astrology

-MXNZd5ae_b9qNBDMQlx.description: Anything worth having is well hidden so one must look very carefully. Use this to spot traps, things normally hidden, or things out of the ordinary.
-MXNZd5ae_b9qNBDMQlx.name: Awareness

-MXNZfcWzax8lEYJe_JK.description: The usefulness of the ability to clamber up things cannot be overstated. Most climbs should be single rolls though longer or more difficult climbs may require multiple rolls. On these climbs consider requiring a number or total or repeated failures to fall off unless it is a particularly  merciless ascent. The GM should use their discretion.
-MXNZfcWzax8lEYJe_JK.name: Climb

-MXNZieBoEeWYMOGrBTV.description: This includes any Skill you might think of that comes under the heading of arts and crafts. Blacksmithing, carpentry, painting, opera singing, anything like that. Roll Under the Skill if you want to do something that knowledge of this Skill would reasonably cover. A carpenter might be able to spot a weak bridge while a blacksmith could shoe a horse or an opera singer could identify an aria. Be flexible and reasonable.
-MXNZieBoEeWYMOGrBTV.name: Crafting Skills

-MXNZmA69QEBIBqjrpDM.description: Covers the use of props to change your appearance. When in disguise you must Roll Under this when someone is liable to see through it. Opposed by Awareness when under scrutiny.
-MXNZmA69QEBIBqjrpDM.name: Disguise

-MXNZoty1rlVaWh0sKeV.description: When making a good impression is important Roll Versus your host’s Etiquette. Represents a mechanical understanding of social conduct and those who are better at it are more discerning.
-MXNZoty1rlVaWh0sKeV.name: Etiquette

-MXNZrLNyE9ax-1WW-3Z.description: Test this to get an idea of how much something is worth.
-MXNZrLNyE9ax-1WW-3Z.name: Evaluate

-MXNZu47lOcNGx7GZ8fg.description: Use Fly much as you would Run. In normal situations this doesn’t need testing, only in chases or high winds, maybe. Anyone attempting to Fly without this Skill must Test every Round to make sure they don’t crash or lose control.
-MXNZu47lOcNGx7GZ8fg.name: Fly

-MXNZxf0QRwxyubX2FBt.description: Test this to navigate between the stars on a ship with golden mirror sails.
-MXNZxf0QRwxyubX2FBt.name: Golden Barge Pilot

-MXN_-1uOOFB8mGzUmpz.description: Used to stitch wounds and apply ointments, stop bleeding, slow poison and the like. Also used for stabilising dying people.
-MXN_-1uOOFB8mGzUmpz.name: Healing

-MXN_1dCNX7Cy-PgZAyx.description: Represents relative competence in specific languages and would only need to be Tested if trying to understand something incredibly arcane or technical. It’s assumed that once you have one point in a language you can understand it passably. You get one tick in a language for every month of intense tuition or complete submersion in it.
-MXN_1dCNX7Cy-PgZAyx.name: Languages

-MXN_4Sis45SRWUoZeqq.description: This allows a character to examine and open locks but does not detect traps. Roll Versus an imaginary locksmith whose Skill is somewhere between 6 and 12 with 6 being easy and 12 being very hard.
-MXN_4Sis45SRWUoZeqq.name: Locks

-MXN_6z_ZtKe5kfI4S7w.description: Use this to gain insight into angles, pressures, numbers, and other such arcane arts. You could, for instance, Test your Mathmology to get a good idea of the surface tension of a ball of inert plasmic goo or to find the fulcrum for tripping a giant.
-MXN_6z_ZtKe5kfI4S7w.name: Mathmology

-MXN_CBjj4H8HPDyVGqZ.description: You may Test this Skill during down time to create a single dose of poison. Pick which kind it is when you make it. This list is not exhaustive — more exotic ones may be available if you possess the knowledge and ingredients. 1d3 Common Poisons of Troika: 1 Causes anyone ingesting it to Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or lose 4d6 Stamina. 2 Add 1 to all Damage Rolls while this is applied to piercing or edged Weapons. If you Roll a 1 for Damage the poison has worn off. 3 Causes anyone ingesting it to fall unconscious for 1d6 hours.
-MXN_CBjj4H8HPDyVGqZ.name: Poison

-MXN_FM1EIwTKP5RfHYo.description: Everyone is assumed to have basic animal riding Skill though anything more than trotting slowly will require some kind of roll to avoid trouble.
-MXN_FM1EIwTKP5RfHYo.name: Ride

-MXN_Hq9Xrea8-sqejI2.description: When it matters how fast you are, or if you can reach somewhere in time, use this. A basic chase is an Roll Versus.
-MXN_Hq9Xrea8-sqejI2.name: Run

-MXN_KQNyBso2DIUTgAx.description: Use of this allows the detection of magic. On a successful Test you focus your inner eye and all sorcerous activity glows faintly for a moment.
-MXN_KQNyBso2DIUTgAx.name: Second Sight

-MXN_NG7xTxs4e3wEjxa.description: Used to identify marks, handshakes, code words, etc. of one specific society. You would, for example, be able to read the secret marks left on people’s door posts by fellow hobos.
-MXN_NG7xTxs4e3wEjxa.name: Secret Signs

-MXN_Pgiz1Kk6q5ajyVZ.description: Steal or hide small things. This is Tested only if someone is actively looking for them. A character may simply declare they are hiding something, only rolling this when the hiddenness is questioned.
-MXN_Pgiz1Kk6q5ajyVZ.name: Sleight of Hand

-MXN_S3vcVNXyfkOevm-.description: The art of remaining unseen. This is Tested only when someone or something is actively trying to detect you. The sneaker would Roll Versus the Awareness of those searching for them; anyone beating the sneaker’s score detects them.
-MXN_S3vcVNXyfkOevm-.name: Sneak

-MXN_UIJNbsuJcstWJtI.description: Used for lifting and breaking things. May also be used to grapple people if no grappling-appropriate Weapon Skill is possessed, though it counts for half rounded up.
-MXN_UIJNbsuJcstWJtI.name: Strength

-MXN_WNEkc14X5YXeGEE.description: Use this while swimming in dangerous waters, diving, holding your breath for long periods, and so on. If you have this Skill you don’t need to roll it for normal conditions. Characters without it are assumed to not be able to swim and need to test Swimming every round they remain in the water or start Drowning (7.9). Receive a penalty to this Skill equal to half the number of item slots filled.
-MXN_WNEkc14X5YXeGEE.name: Swim

-MXN_Ytl7yAvfrpfKoQU.description: Used to stalk prey and find tracks. When stalking a quarry this is treated as an opposed Roll Versus the opponent’s Tracking or Sneaking.
-MXN_Ytl7yAvfrpfKoQU.name: Tracking

-MXN_aUNiEKhNgJ-qSSt.description: Use this to set and disarm traps. When setting traps Roll Under your Trapping Skill and describe how the trap is made with the materials at hand. When someone wishes to disarm a trap they must Roll Versus the original trap-setter’s Trapping Skill. If the GM doesn’t know what that number should be assume 6 to be pretty simple while 12 is incredibly hard. Scale it between those as appropriate.
-MXN_aUNiEKhNgJ-qSSt.name: Trapping

-MXN_dPyHTChcP_rq_is.description: You may use this Skill in place of your Weapon Skill while fighting in confined spaces where you would otherwise be unable to swing your Weapon about. You ignore all penalties the GM might associate with fighting in such a situation.
-MXN_dPyHTChcP_rq_is.name: Tunnel Fighting

-MXN_fzGgIoLU6MMG_Jr.description: Choose what general category of Weapons this covers when you take this Skill. Roll Versus during combat when using the appropriate method of assault. The GM is encouraged to allow Weapon categories to be broadly applicable, such as Glaive Fighting being equivalent to Polearm Fighting.
-MXN_fzGgIoLU6MMG_Jr.name: Weapon Fighting

-MXNnoDzUE72CGri4xkY.description: Cause a subject to be fixed in place. While they are so held they do not move, breathe, fall, perspire, acquire, or otherwise change. They are totally immune to harm, in fact. Lasts for 3 minutes.
-MXNnoDzUE72CGri4xkY.name: Affix

-MXNo4Om47ZHQ2qxqh98.description: The College of Friends always sends out its Factotums on nights after Amity classes. Clearing out the bars and brothels of their drunken apprentices is tiring work. Use of this Spell causes the target to Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or become very friendly towards the wizard, as though they were an old friend. They will not act irrationally, though, and if they were already a bit of a boor this might not change much.
-MXNo4Om47ZHQ2qxqh98.name: Amity

-MXNo7LKzplJwtnM2PX4.description: Cause inanimate objects to question their place. One object up to the size of a human baby may be caused to hop around and do whatever else the wizard wishes.
-MXNo7LKzplJwtnM2PX4.name: Animate

-MXNoCh4T0SypuNvrYWb.description: Evocatively named but actually quite mundane. The wizard whispers to an object and that object then seeks out and vigorously and repeatedly bumps into the desired target. Obviously if you whisper to a poisoned dagger the result is one thing while doing it to a letter is another. Travels any distance and always arrives (eventually).
-MXNoCh4T0SypuNvrYWb.name: Assassin’s Dagger

-MXNoFzU70T8HP7ptHz5.description: The wizard undergoes a distressing transformation into an inanimate object no larger than a piano and no smaller than a cup. Lasts until ended.
-MXNoFzU70T8HP7ptHz5.name: Assume Shape

-MXNoJt4fKvfA1-7zb2D.description: The Sorcerers of the Academy of Doors are most famous for this one Spell. With it they may reach through any portal and into another known receptacle. For example they might use it to reach through to a safe in their manse via their purse. This Spell only allows partial translocation— the wizard cannot fully or permanently enter.
-MXNoJt4fKvfA1-7zb2D.name: Astral Reach

-MXNoNjsWnhUQhvsg6Uz.description: The wizard speaks nonsense while watching the intended target, causing their words to trip and confuse. This may be done under their breath and relatively subtly.
-MXNoNjsWnhUQhvsg6Uz.name: Babble

-MXNoRaWOWHuMv50qH-b.description: The wizard explains, clearly, sternly, why it is impossible that the spirit could be here at this time. The spirit must Test its Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or be sent to somewhere less improbable.
-MXNoRaWOWHuMv50qH-b.name: Banish Spirit

-MXNoV0-r3TMl_DP9KHn.description: A wizard’s touch can shake up someone’s mind like a snow globe. The target makes all rolls at a -1 penalty until their head clears. Lasts for 3 minutes.
-MXNoV0-r3TMl_DP9KHn.name: Befuddle

-MXNoYtZ9wxe8gl7Uy_g.description: Smear a small amount of a demon’s blood on yourself to become completely invisible to them, even if you attack or speak to them, for 6 hours.
-MXNoYtZ9wxe8gl7Uy_g.name: Blood Shroud

-MXNoayn3NySBGglLIXI.description: The wizard’s hands work elemental material as though it were soft clay. Fire, stone, goo, earth, fog, all of it behaves like clay under their touch. Lasts for 9 minutes.
-MXNoayn3NySBGglLIXI.name: Breach

-MXNoeGvhsa28-4Ylfdt.description: You snap a twig or other brittle object to cause an injury in another. They must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or suffer a broken bone.
-MXNoeGvhsa28-4Ylfdt.name: Brittle Twigs

-MXNohYyFQY-9vBGXwYF.description: The Wizard-Knights are most famous for their remote combat whereby they swing their Silver Swords seemingly at nothing only for their opponents, many metres away, to be torn to tatters. This Spell can be used in place of a melee attack by Rolling Versus as normal and inflicting Damage according to the Weapon used. May only be used against targets within clear sight.
-MXNohYyFQY-9vBGXwYF.name: Callous Strike

-MXNokqjR6qTIRic_L_V.description: This Spell turns one’s heart into a burning ember of grief. Those under its effect are so consumed by grief that they are immune to mind controlling effects and the non-physical impact of pain. Lasts until the next rest.
-MXNokqjR6qTIRic_L_V.name: Coal Resolve

-MXNonl2or_WcwQq7ss4.description: A popular Spell that turns troublesome folk into humiliated animals. The target must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or be turned into an insignificant creature of the wizard’s choice. Lasts forever.
-MXNonl2or_WcwQq7ss4.name: Cockroach

-MXNorOdAKh0YQVYmC9d.description: Creates a mysterious and specifically shaped cone of air focused on a touched target’s head. They may continue to breathe the freshest of air for 12 minutes.
-MXNorOdAKh0YQVYmC9d.name: Cone of Air

-MXNouAATb1rqjC5XbON.description: Summon a stationary, perfect sphere of darkness up to five metres from the wizard for up to 3 minutes.
-MXNouAATb1rqjC5XbON.name: Darkness

-MXNoxK7vHhZqZ_UbJTS.description: The wizard reaches into their sockets and extricates their eyes. Thus freed, the dark void behind can see perfectly well in pitch blackness and suffer excruciating pain in light (-4 penalty to all rolls). Be careful not to lose those eyeballs as re-inserting them is the only way to end the Spell.
-MXNoxK7vHhZqZ_UbJTS.name: Darksee

-MXNozdgcmt-PaKQ2PDv.description: Cause something to Test its Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or reduce its size by half. Lasts 3 minutes.
-MXNozdgcmt-PaKQ2PDv.name: Diminish

-MXNp11yPXCvPvAN4bvM.description: Cause a target’s lungs to fill with water. They must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies). If they fail they start to Drown (7.9) and are incapacitated as water pours from their mouth. They may Test again once per Turn until they pass, at which point the Spell ends.
-MXNp11yPXCvPvAN4bvM.name: Drown

-MXNp4MK-06IRqFIYHaD.description: The wizard hikes up their wizard robe and stomps their wizard feet. An area 30 metres around them suffers a massive earthquake. Everyone must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or fall through a crack in the earth, taking falling Damage and being stuck in a bloody great big hole (7.8.1). Buildings may be wrecked unless especially sturdy.
-MXNp4MK-06IRqFIYHaD.name: Earthquake

-MXNpGPymkscxAJVkb87.description: A simple but effective summoning of fire. Flames the size of a small bonfire appear somewhere within 12 metres of the wizard. Once present there is no accounting for its actions. Exchange
-MXNpGPymkscxAJVkb87.name: Ember

-MXNpJ49MNVMsd1Jygdp.description: What looks like a hug is in fact fell wizardry! The wizard bumps into another and exchanges bodies. Lasts until the wizard chooses to end it but they must be within sight of their own body for this to happen.
-MXNpJ49MNVMsd1Jygdp.name: Shape

-MXNpLeMIRBoebfWD221.description: The Red Priests posit that all negative behaviour is a symptom of some level of possession, or at least direct influence, by the forces of Change, unwitting agents of Mass in need of healing. The wizard throws salt at their target and Rolls Versus the possessing spirit to cast it out. In the case of a Fumble the spirit is drawn into and possesses the wizard.
-MXNpLeMIRBoebfWD221.name: Exorcism

-MXNpOtzFt4pHoPnMz8k.description: So simple that it’s arguably not even a Spell but rather a premeditated failure of catastrophic proportions. The wizard causes a one cubic metre object to explode and deal Damage to everyone within 24 metres depending on proximity. Those within 6 metres take Damage as a Gigantic Beast, within 12 as a Large Beast, 18 as a Modest Beast and 24 as a Small Beast.
-MXNpOtzFt4pHoPnMz8k.name: Explode

-MXNpTJyKvRW02CDjOb5.description: Endows the wizard with engorged, plate-like eyes that are able to see in minute detail for miles around but are unable to see anything up close. Lasts until ended.
-MXNpTJyKvRW02CDjOb5.name: Farseeing

-MXNpVr2CaH7jIr_45mp.description: In the eyes of one poor target the wizard grows into a primal monster from the depths of their lizard brain. They will attempt to flee and if flight is impossible they will curl up in a ball and whimper. They may Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) to resist the illusion.
-MXNpVr2CaH7jIr_45mp.name: Fear

-MXNpZHR9m5GGfxbFB-w.description: When wizards lose their glasses they mumble to themselves until they turn up. The thing being sought must be a specific object, not a general category or type, and the direction is only given in terms of compass points.
-MXNpZHR9m5GGfxbFB-w.name: Find

-MXNplmZsZm7Wn8OaMz3.description:
Shoot impressive flames from your fingertips, dealing Damage to one target within 20 metres.

Damage Roll:
1-2 : 3
3: 5
4: 7
5: 9
6: 12
7+: 16
-MXNplmZsZm7Wn8OaMz3.name: Fire Bolt

-MXNpoaz4q7SyauvGved.description: The wizard claps neatly and issues forth the light of a thousand suns from their hands. All within 20 metres must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or be blinded for 1d6 minutes.
-MXNpoaz4q7SyauvGved.name: Flash

-MXNprogo3XQkpgjx_pb.description: The wizard may permanently gift a touched subject with gills, replacing their usual breathing arrangement if they fail to Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies). Useful for underwater excursions but less so when inflicted upon a chap in the middle of town. The wizard may end this at will.
-MXNprogo3XQkpgjx_pb.name: Gills

-MXNpuKIl1oLWPQvdxl3.description: Cause an item to grow half its size again if it fails to Test its Luck (or Skill for Enemies). Lasts for 3 minutes
-MXNpuKIl1oLWPQvdxl3.name: Grow

-MXNvid303xysJafjeFa.description: Animate hands spring forth from an inanimate surface and perform any task the wizard requires but are limited to being rooted to the spot from which they sprang. They last until the wizard wills it or leaves the location.
-MXNvid303xysJafjeFa.name: Helping Hands

-MXNvm3q9-nBZsO5ob57.description: The wizard waves their hands in the air like they just don’t care, which, being wizards, they likely don’t. A mighty gust knocks everyone over within 30 metres who fails to Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies), dealing 1d3 Damage and making an awful mess. Lasts for 10 minutes. Test Luck every Turn if not taking cover or else take further Damage.
-MXNvm3q9-nBZsO5ob57.name: Hurricane

-MXNvqe0T6auhasGbhEV.description: Those viewing this illusion may Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) to unveil the trickery. Lasts until the wizard leaves or falls asleep. (Costs 2 per viewer)
-MXNvqe0T6auhasGbhEV.name: Illusion

-MXNvu1R5kxsL19JMstU.description: The wizard turns flesh into refractive crystal sheets. It’s very uncomfortable and you make a slight shish-ing sound as you move but are quite invisible and don’t suffer from the usual limitations of illusions. Lasts for 3 minutes after which you noisily reform into dull and frustratingly opaque flesh.
-MXNvu1R5kxsL19JMstU.name: Invisibility

-MXNvwfrrGsTIZs-I7h1.description: The common man does not appreciate exactly how close flesh and iron are when considered relative to, say, flesh and the smell of hot tea. With some slight convincing the wizard may cause a target’s flesh to behave as though it had the desirable properties of metal. They get +1 Skill and immunity to modestly proportioned fires for 3 minutes.
-MXNvwfrrGsTIZs-I7h1.name: Ironhand

-MXNw46gRUjkRmtHd2rl.description:
The mischievous apprentice’s favourite Spell, Jolt sends an arc of electricity from the wizard’s outstretched hand towards a target. Ignores Armour. 

Damage:

1-2: 2
3-4: 3
5: 5
6: 7
7+: 9
-MXNw46gRUjkRmtHd2rl.name: Jolt

-MXNw7-RHT8BxCxZmt2O.description: The wizard forms a mouth with their hands through which they can speak any language. They can simultaneously cup their other hand to their ear to understand them in return. Lasts for one conversation.
-MXNw7-RHT8BxCxZmt2O.name: Languages

-MXNw9LY_Bf9shuFyNzx.description: The necromancer must place their hands on a living subject and allow their fingertips to transform into sucking apertures which drain the victim of blood. Deal 2d6 Damage to your victim and regain half as much Stamina.
-MXNw9LY_Bf9shuFyNzx.name: Leech

-MXNwBl4y9LrwF24Mab5.description: Elevates the wizard or another on the backs of tiny invisible sprites who answer only to their summoner. May float about for 3 minutes.
-MXNwBl4y9LrwF24Mab5.name: Levitate

-MXNwEZAWZhMrdXESIIy.description: Created by the Horizon Knights to enable them to take the fight to the Nothing, they would cast this on their squires and dive off the edge of creation. While this Spell lasts the wizard’s essential bodily functions are linked to another, thereby enabling them to breath or eat for the recipient. They will need to breathe and eat for two, which makes it hard to do anything useful while linked. The Spell lasts for a day, until cancelled, or until the death of the linked person. Note if the linked person dies, starves, or is choked you will suffer equally.
-MXNwEZAWZhMrdXESIIy.name: Life Line

-MXNwGgdIgJHQiQT1VEW.description: Create an ethereal orb of light that glows like a torch. Lasts 6 hours and can be extinguished at will.
-MXNwGgdIgJHQiQT1VEW.name: Light

-MXNwIPc_FDHqSV7mG0s.description: Magically lock an object. The object must have a lockable aspect to it but is now magically sealed. Permanent until undone or dismissed.
-MXNwIPc_FDHqSV7mG0s.name: Lock

-MXNwL4nuhlTTWfWufRh.description: In the minds of others the wizard appears to be, in fact, three wizards. All three will perform the same actions in unison, offering attackers only a 1 in 3 chance of targeting the right wizard. Lasts for 12 minutes.
-MXNwL4nuhlTTWfWufRh.name: Mirror Selves

-MXNwNSVerPDhlbiWSkr.description: As everyone knows, wizards are excellent ventriloquists, so good, in fact, that they can throw their voice inside another’s mouth. They can target anyone within sight and transmit a short sentence.
-MXNwNSVerPDhlbiWSkr.name: Netter

-MXNwPS7LhXSHy2eAs6P.description: The wizard chooses a reality wherein the lock was open all along. May be used to open any mundane door or container and counteract a Lock Spell.
-MXNwPS7LhXSHy2eAs6P.name: Open

-MXNwR_DhJR_g9M-R-6n.description: Open up the mind to universal love and cause two subjects to Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or cease hostilities. They will still defend themselves if attacked but will at least appreciate the pettiness of it.
-MXNwR_DhJR_g9M-R-6n.name: Peace

-MXNwUKqz4oMOOd65FY3.description: When cast upon a liquid this Spell causes it to become deadly poison. The liquid deals 4 Damage if drunk and 1 Damage per Turn until the target successfully Tests their Luck (or Skill for Enemies). The liquid loses its potency after an hour.
-MXNwUKqz4oMOOd65FY3.name: Poison

-MXNwffpdpcIX9pss_Oq.description:
Necromancers, known for their social inadequacy, often find themselves having to make friends. This Spell requires a fresh, or at least whole and lubricated, corpse. The wizard rolls 2d6 plus their Posthumous Vitality Skill Total and consults the following chart (13+ counts for an Advancement tick): 

4-12 Nothing happens. 
13-14 The vitality is clumsily applied, causing the body to explode messily. A new one will need to be found. 
15-16 The creature is animated and will last for 24 hours before literally falling to pieces. 
17+ Perfect reanimation. The creature will last until destroyed.
-MXNwffpdpcIX9pss_Oq.name: Posthumous Vitality

-MXNwj0vWJQrVawerN74.description: This Spell creates the sense of being watched by a patriarchal figure. Some find it comforting, others, not so much.
-MXNwj0vWJQrVawerN74.name: Presence

-MXNwlqzpyK8T0L97aUu.description: This Spell prevents the wizard from getting rained upon for one shower.
-MXNwlqzpyK8T0L97aUu.name: Protection from Rain

-MXNwoqPorER9_lOQVi5.description: The recipient’s eyes glow purple as they experience an alternative reality where people are kind, their surroundings are beautiful, their food is indulgent, and so on. This doesn’t change the reality of things but it does make them more palatable. Lasts until they want it to end.
-MXNwoqPorER9_lOQVi5.name: Purple Lens

-MXNwrb_tORAeVlSwSgL.description: Snuff a small flame with the wave of a hand.
-MXNwrb_tORAeVlSwSgL.name: Quench

-MXNwuNFoI5mcXz7Pdd8.description: The wizard can get the answer to one question from the entrails of a living creature. The size and importance of the creature influences the level of knowledge gained. Small, common animals are able to offer yes or no answers, oxen can predict things obtusely, lamassu may offer explicit and thorough advice.
-MXNwuNFoI5mcXz7Pdd8.name: Read Entrails

-MXNwxBRMIS5jqBM2g-v.description: Rather than physical stars the wizard navigates by astral starlight that peeks through the veil. This Spell enables the wizard to get a reasonable sense of direction regardless of any obscuring factors.
-MXNwxBRMIS5jqBM2g-v.name: Read Stars

-MXNx-8FcM1VZgQdZsqX.description: The wizard rubs a surface vigorously, making it translucent. Can penetrate up to 12 inches of material. Lead and Silver are immune
-MXNx-8FcM1VZgQdZsqX.name: See Through

-MXNx2S_p8s8jn1dLnsv.description: The wizard plucks a bit of their mind out like candy floss and leaves it stuck to a wall somewhere. This psychic presence is invisible to the naked eye but extends the wizard’s senses to that spot for the duration. While it lasts the wizard suffers -1 to all rolls due to the incredible confusion this generates. If the shard is discovered and harmed the wizard will lose 2d6 Stamina due to the shock.
-MXNx2S_p8s8jn1dLnsv.name: Sentry

-MXNx545puIYGJdPcgng.description: The wizard may wildly gesticulate at a brittle object no larger than an umbrella and cause it to shatter into a million pieces. Living targets may Test their Luck to avoid this unpleasant Spell.
-MXNx545puIYGJdPcgng.name: Shatter

-MXNx81bEhRMpzhwc4Xk.description: Necromancers often talk to skulls. Sometimes they talk back. Use of this Spell enables speaking with the dead, who answer one question per casting. Requires a skull.
-MXNx81bEhRMpzhwc4Xk.name: Skeletal Counsel

-MXNxAjwXSDGHiQ-l4rg.description: The wizard convinces a target to forgo wakefulness for a time, causing them to sleep until woken unless they successfully Test their Luck. Remember: fighting is loud.
-MXNxAjwXSDGHiQ-l4rg.name: Sleep

-MXNxD5Qu6SVMGbrPxS4.description: Requires mirrors or other highly reflective surfaces. The wizard stands between two reflective surfaces so that they are infinitely repeated. They then step out from between them but as a different incidence of themselves. To those watching the wizard moves in the direction not seen and reappears between two mirrors elsewhere. If the location has been compromised the wizard arrives in a random mirrored location somewhere across the million crystal spheres.
-MXNxD5Qu6SVMGbrPxS4.name: Slide Skywards

-MXNxGNIVuZ_BL9oThtQ.description: The wizard creates a 5th dimensional orb above their head. All intelligent beings looking at it must Test their Luck or marvel at it for 3 minutes.
-MXNxGNIVuZ_BL9oThtQ.name: Starry Orb

-MXNxJM90yI6zsPNJOny.description: The wizard or a target of their choosing may travel to any location within a single sphere instantly. If unfamiliar with the location they must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or be thrown wildly off course to potentially devastating results.
-MXNxJM90yI6zsPNJOny.name: Teleport

-MXNxLbLBoarAbTGOPKE.description: The wizard can cause their nose to exist in multiple alternative realities, travel through various spheres, and enable the olfactory sensation of thought. Emotions, attitudes, and underlying feelings can be smelled. No words or images are formed, just impressions. Any strong odour will cause this Spell to fail.
-MXNxLbLBoarAbTGOPKE.name: Thought Vapour

-MXNxNvWoDCJ_W_0njUy.description: The wizard raises their arms and shouts something suitably ominous. All within 24 metres must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or be deafened by a riotous roll of thunder. Luck or no, they will be mightily impressed.
-MXNxNvWoDCJ_W_0njUy.name: Thunder

-MXNxRA6axgKTJSk8bb8.description: Beware! If a wizard screws their nose and twists their fingers at you then a Tongue Twister is coming your way. The target must Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies) or have their tongue literally tied in knots. This requires some time and a fair bit of patience to disentangle.
-MXNxRA6axgKTJSk8bb8.name: Tongue Twister

-MXNxTkqGN0Ff0Ziv7iY.description: Those who study the dead consider it necessary to develop a profound sympathy with their subject — how can you speak with the dead if you don’t understand the dead? Torpor helps build post-mortem empathy by causing the necromancer to temporarily die. Bodily functions are halted, no food, water, or air is needed, and they are, by most vulgar definitions of the word, dead. The Spell lasts until ended by the wizard, who remains vaguely aware of their surroundings to the extent of being conscious of sound and movement but not of what is said or who is saying it. They will still take Damage from bodily abuse while under the effect and can indeed become irretrievably dead
-MXNxTkqGN0Ff0Ziv7iY.name: Torpor

-MXNxVyivoQi61yG5_c4.description: The wizard focuses their sight on the unambiguous truth of matter, enabling them to see through illusions for the next 10 minutes.
-MXNxVyivoQi61yG5_c4.name: True Seeing

-MXNxkHtQN3wteOXvtCY.description: The wizard disentangles a Spell from this instance of reality. To do so they must Roll Versus the original casting if disentanglement is possible at all. (Double cost of original spell)
-MXNxkHtQN3wteOXvtCY.name: Undo

-MXNxnsqFklfi-K7jH8D.description: A handy Spell only requiring the flick of a wrist. In response to being fired upon the wizard may cast this Spell to cause the missile to be deflected.
-MXNxnsqFklfi-K7jH8D.name: Ward

-MXNxrRIE4-dUn1ypt_f.description: What they call a wall is in fact a dome, but wizards always have worked in mysterious ways. The wall is a shimmering bubble that causes 1d6 Damage when touched. Nothing may pass without the wizard’s permission (it is recommended that they remember to allow air). Lasts for 12 minutes.
-MXNxrRIE4-dUn1ypt_f.name: Wall of Power

-MXNxuQum-eO8d_ZNUM3.description: Whether this is opening a portal to the plane of slime or channelling the sprites of sickness, all can agree that it is quite disgusting. The wizard blows forth the “web” from their nose and all in a cone extending 12 metres in front of the wizard are trapped unless they Test their Luck (or Skill for Enemies). Each Turn anything passing through or out of it must repeat the Test or become stuck. Dries up after 12 rounds.
-MXNxuQum-eO8d_ZNUM3.name: Web

-MXNxxjufVIGAAY9sED0.description: No one knows what this does but everyone who has cast it disappears instantly, never to be seen again.
-MXNxxjufVIGAAY9sED0.name: Zed
